7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1046, L.D. 1588, “An Act to Ensure
10 Transparency in Student Transfer Requests”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 20-A MRSA §5205, sub-§6, ¶A, as amended by PL 2013, c. 456, §1, is
14 further amended by enacting at the end a new last blocked paragraph to read:
15 By July 1st of each year, a school administrative unit shall report to the commissioner
16 the total number of transfer requests presented to the school administrative unit in the
17 last year, including requests to transfer to or from the school administrative unit. The
18 report must also state the number of transfers accepted and the number of transfers
19 denied. The commissioner shall annually publish this data on the department's publicly
20 accessible website.
21 Sec. 2. 20-A MRSA §5205, sub-§6, ¶B, as amended by PL 2013, c. 456, §2, is
22 further amended by enacting at the end a new first blocked paragraph to read:
23 The commissioner shall publish on the department's publicly accessible website the
24 number of transfer determinations, the number of transfers accepted and the number of
25 transfers denied.'
26 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
27 number to read consecutively.
28 SUMMARY
2299 This amendment removes from the bill the requirement that school administrative units
3300 provide the written description for each student transfer denial to the Commissioner of
3311 Education.
